Modifications
-------------

The following modifications have been applied to the upstream codebase
in this derivative work:

  - package.json: added "main", "types", and "exports" fields so the
    package is consumable as a library, in addition to its existing
    CLI binaries. Renamed the package to "freee-mcp-core" to avoid
    npm namespace conflict with the upstream "freee-mcp" package.
  - src/lib.ts: new file. Re-exports the public library API (createMcpServer,
    addAuthenticationTools, addFileUploadTool, registerSkillResources,
    makeApiRequest, loadConfig, etc.) for downstream consumers.
  - src/skills-path.ts: new file. Resolves the bundled skills/ directory
    via import.meta.url so consumers can locate it at runtime.
  - src/mcp/skill-resources.ts: new file. Registers bundled skill content
    as MCP resources (URI scheme skill://) so any MCP client can read
    skill markdown via the standard resources/list and resources/read
    methods.
  - src/cli/skills.ts: new file. Implements install/update/uninstall
    helpers for skill content, plus reusable *From(srcDir, opts) variants
    for downstream consumers that bundle additional skills.
  - src/index.ts: extended the CLI dispatcher with install-skills,
    update-skills, and uninstall-skills subcommands.
  - src/mcp/handlers.ts: createMcpServer now auto-registers bundled skill
    resources by default (opt-out via { skipBundledSkills: true }).
  - build.ts: added emission of dist/lib.js (library bundle, non-minified,
    deps external) and dist/*.d.ts (TypeScript declarations) alongside
    the existing CLI bin output.
  - package.json files array: added skills/, openapi/, and NOTICE so they
    ship in the npm tarball.

